Minister of Culture of Kyrgyzstan participated in the International Tourism Exhibition in China :: Kabar - Kyrgyz National News Agency
Bishkek, June 21 / Kabar /. Minister of Culture, Information and Tourism of Kyrgyzstan Sultan Rayev took part in the 9th International Tourism Exhibition, which was held June 19-20 in the Xinjiang Uighur Autonomous Region (XUAR) of China. The press service of the Culture Ministry reports.
Leading tour operators and media representatives of Europe and Asia took part in the exhibition. At the opening ceremony S.Rayev presenting tourism opportunities of Kyrgyzstan, said that this industry is very promising.
Within the framework of the exhibition the Kyrgyz Minister held bilateral meetings with the leaders of Xinjiang. At the meeting with deputy governor of the Autonomous Region Shi Da Gang and Director of the Agency for Tourism Li Vey the sides discussed the development of relations in the sphere of tourism.
As a result of this international exhibition agreements were signed with five leading travel companies of China. 
